{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We all make decisions every day; we want to know"},{"time":2000,"text":"what the right thing is to do -- in domains from the financial"},{"time":5000,"text":"to the gastronomic to the professional to the romantic."},{"time":9000,"text":"And surely, if somebody could really tell us how to do"},{"time":12000,"text":"exactly the right thing at all possible times,"},{"time":15000,"text":"that would be a tremendous gift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"It turns out that, in fact, the world was given this gift in 1738"},{"time":23000,"text":"by a Dutch polymath named Daniel Bernoulli."},{"time":26000,"text":"And what I want to talk to you about today is what that gift is,"},{"time":29000,"text":"and I also want to explain to you why it is"},{"time":32000,"text":"that it hasn't made a damn bit of difference."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"Now, this is Bernoulli's gift. This is a direct quote."},{"time":40000,"text":"And if it looks like Greek to you, it's because, well, it's Greek."},{"time":44000,"text":"But the simple English translation -- much less precise,"},{"time":48000,"text":"but it captures the gist of what Bernoulli had to say -- was this:"},{"time":52000,"text":"The expected value of any of our actions --"},{"time":54000,"text":"that is, the goodness that we can count on getting --"},{"time":58000,"text":"is the product of two simple things:"},{"time":60000,"text":"the odds that this action will allow us to gain something,"},{"time":64000,"text":"and the value of that gain to us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67000,"text":"In a sense, what Bernoulli was saying is,"},{"time":69000,"text":"if we can estimate and multiply these two things,"},{"time":72000,"text":"we will always know precisely how we should behave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"Now, this simple equation, even for those of you"},{"time":78000,"text":"who don't like equations, is something that you're quite used to."},{"time":81000,"text":"Here's an example: if I were to tell you, let's play"},{"time":84000,"text":"a little coin toss game, and I'm going to flip a coin,"},{"time":87000,"text":"and if it comes up heads, I'm going to pay you 10 dollars,"},{"time":90000,"text":"but you have to pay four dollars for the privilege of playing with me,"},{"time":94000,"text":"most of you would say, sure, I'll take that bet. Because you know"},{"time":97000,"text":"that the odds of you winning are one half, the gain if you do is 10 dollars,"},{"time":102000,"text":"that multiplies to five, and that's more"},{"time":104000,"text":"than I'm charging you to play. So, the answer is, yes."},{"time":108000,"text":"This is what statisticians technically call a damn fine bet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"Now, the idea is simple when we're applying it to coin tosses,"},{"time":115000,"text":"but in fact, it's not very simple in everyday life."},{"time":119000,"text":"People are horrible at estimating both of these things,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and that's what I want to talk to you about today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125000,"text":"There are two kinds of errors people make when trying to decide"},{"time":128000,"text":"what the right thing is to do, and those are"},{"time":130000,"text":"errors in estimating the odds that they're going to succeed,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and errors in estimating the value of their own success."},{"time":137000,"text":"Now, let me talk about the first one first."},{"time":141000,"text":"Calculating odds would seem to be something rather easy:"},{"time":143000,"text":"there are six sides to a die, two sides to a coin, 52 cards in a deck."},{"time":147000,"text":"You all know what the likelihood is of pulling the ace of spades"},{"time":151000,"text":"or of flipping a heads."},{"time":152000,"text":"But as it turns out, this is not a very easy idea to apply"},{"time":157000,"text":"in everyday life. That's why Americans spend more --"},{"time":160000,"text":"I should say, lose more -- gambling"},{"time":163000,"text":"than on all other forms of entertainment combined."},{"time":168000,"text":"The reason is, this isn't how people do odds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"The way people figure odds"},{"time":172000,"text":"requires that we first talk a bit about pigs."},{"time":175000,"text":"Now, the question I'm going to put to you is whether you think"},{"time":177000,"text":"there are more dogs or pigs on leashes"},{"time":180000,"text":"observed in any particular day in Oxford."},{"time":183000,"text":"And of course, you all know that the answer is dogs."},{"time":185000,"text":"And the way that you know that the answer is dogs is"},{"time":188000,"text":"you quickly reviewed in memory the times"},{"time":190000,"text":"you've seen dogs and pigs on leashes."},{"time":192000,"text":"It was very easy to remember seeing dogs,"},{"time":195000,"text":"not so easy to remember pigs. And each one of you assumed"},{"time":198000,"text":"that if dogs on leashes came more quickly to your mind,"},{"time":202000,"text":"then dogs on leashes are more probable."},{"time":204000,"text":"That's not a bad rule of thumb, except when it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"So, for example, here's a word puzzle."},{"time":211000,"text":"Are there more four-letter English words"},{"time":213000,"text":"with R in the third place or R in the first place?"},{"time":217000,"text":"Well, you check memory very briefly, make a quick scan,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and it's awfully easy to say to yourself, Ring, Rang, Rung,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and very hard to say to yourself, Pare, Park: they come more slowly."},{"time":230000,"text":"But in fact, there are many more words in the English language"},{"time":232000,"text":"with R in the third than the first place."},{"time":235000,"text":"The reason words with R in the third place come slowly to your mind"},{"time":239000,"text":"isn't because they're improbable, unlikely or infrequent."},{"time":242000,"text":"It's because the mind recalls words by their first letter."},{"time":246000,"text":"You kind of shout out the sound, S -- and the word comes."},{"time":249000,"text":"It's like the dictionary;"},{"time":250000,"text":"it's hard to look things up by the third letter."},{"time":253000,"text":"So, this is an example of how this idea that"},{"time":255000,"text":"the quickness with which things come to mind"},{"time":257000,"text":"can give you a sense of their probability --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259000,"text":"how this idea could lead you astray. It's not just puzzles, though."},{"time":263000,"text":"For example, when Americans are asked to estimate the odds"},{"time":266000,"text":"that they will die in a variety of interesting ways --"},{"time":269000,"text":"these are estimates of number of deaths per year"},{"time":272000,"text":"per 200 million U.S. citizens."},{"time":274000,"text":"And these are just ordinary people like yourselves who are asked"},{"time":276000,"text":"to guess how many people die from tornado, fireworks, asthma, drowning, etc."},{"time":280000,"text":"Compare these to the actual numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"Now, you see a very interesting pattern here, which is first of all,"},{"time":286000,"text":"two things are vastly over-estimated, namely tornadoes and fireworks."},{"time":291000,"text":"Two things are vastly underestimated:"},{"time":293000,"text":"dying by drowning and dying by asthma. Why?"},{"time":296000,"text":"When was the last time that you picked up a newspaper"},{"time":299000,"text":"and the headline was, \"Boy dies of Asthma?\""},{"time":302000,"text":"It's not interesting because it's so common."},{"time":305000,"text":"It's very easy for all of us to bring to mind instances"},{"time":309000,"text":"of news stories or newsreels where we've seen"},{"time":312000,"text":"tornadoes devastating cities, or some poor schmuck"},{"time":314000,"text":"who's blown his hands off with a firework on the Fourth of July."},{"time":318000,"text":"Drownings and asthma deaths don't get much coverage."},{"time":321000,"text":"They don't come quickly to mind, and as a result,"},{"time":323000,"text":"we vastly underestimate them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"Indeed, this is kind of like the Sesame Street game"},{"time":327000,"text":"of \"Which thing doesn't belong?\" And you're right to say"},{"time":331000,"text":"it's the swimming pool that doesn't belong, because the swimming pool"},{"time":334000,"text":"is the only thing on this slide that's actually very dangerous."},{"time":338000,"text":"The way that more of you are likely to die than the combination"},{"time":340000,"text":"of all three of the others that you see on the slide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"The lottery is an excellent example, of course -- an excellent test-case"},{"time":348000,"text":"of people's ability to compute probabilities."},{"time":351000,"text":"And economists -- forgive me, for those of you who play the lottery --"},{"time":354000,"text":"but economists, at least among themselves, refer to the lottery"},{"time":357000,"text":"as a stupidity tax, because the odds of getting any payoff"},{"time":362000,"text":"by investing your money in a lottery ticket"},{"time":364000,"text":"are approximately equivalent to flushing the money"},{"time":366000,"text":"directly down the toilet -- which, by the way,"},{"time":368000,"text":"doesn't require that you actually go to the store and buy anything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372000,"text":"Why in the world would anybody ever play the lottery?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Well, there are many answers, but one answer surely is,"},{"time":378000,"text":"we see a lot of winners. Right? When this couple wins the lottery,"},{"time":382000,"text":"or Ed McMahon shows up at your door with this giant check --"},{"time":385000,"text":"how the hell do you cash things that size, I don't know."},{"time":388000,"text":"We see this on TV; we read about it in the paper."},{"time":391000,"text":"When was the last time that you saw extensive interviews"},{"time":394000,"text":"with everybody who lost?"},{"time":396000,"text":"Indeed, if we required that television stations run"},{"time":399000,"text":"a 30-second interview with each loser"},{"time":401000,"text":"every time they interview a winner, the 100 million losers"},{"time":405000,"text":"in the last lottery would require nine-and-a-half years"},{"time":408000,"text":"of your undivided attention just to watch them say,"},{"time":411000,"text":"\"Me? I lost.\" \"Me? I lost.\""},{"time":414000,"text":"Now, if you watch nine-and-a-half years of television --"},{"time":416000,"text":"no sleep, no potty breaks -- and you saw loss after loss after loss,"},{"time":421000,"text":"and then at the end there's 30 seconds of, \"and I won,\""},{"time":423000,"text":"the likelihood that you would play the lottery is very small."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"Look, I can prove this to you: here's a little lottery."},{"time":429000,"text":"There's 10 tickets in this lottery."},{"time":431000,"text":"Nine of them have been sold to these individuals."},{"time":434000,"text":"It costs you a dollar to buy the ticket and, if you win,"},{"time":437000,"text":"you get 20 bucks. Is this a good bet?"},{"time":439000,"text":"Well, Bernoulli tells us it is."},{"time":440000,"text":"The expected value of this lottery is two dollars;"},{"time":443000,"text":"this is a lottery in which you should invest your money."},{"time":446000,"text":"And most people say, \"OK, I'll play.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"Now, a slightly different version of this lottery:"},{"time":451000,"text":"imagine that the nine tickets are all owned"},{"time":453000,"text":"by one fat guy named Leroy."},{"time":455000,"text":"Leroy has nine tickets; there's one left."},{"time":457000,"text":"Do you want it? Most people won't play this lottery."},{"time":460000,"text":"Now, you can see the odds of winning haven't changed,"},{"time":462000,"text":"but it's now fantastically easy to imagine who's going to win."},{"time":467000,"text":"It's easy to see Leroy getting the check, right?"},{"time":470000,"text":"You can't say to yourself, \"I'm as likely to win as anybody,\""},{"time":472000,"text":"because you're not as likely to win as Leroy."},{"time":475000,"text":"The fact that all those tickets are owned by one guy"},{"time":477000,"text":"changes your decision to play,"},{"time":479000,"text":"even though it does nothing whatsoever to the odds."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482000,"text":"Now, estimating odds, as difficult as it may seem, is a piece of cake"},{"time":487000,"text":"compared to trying to estimate value:"},{"time":489000,"text":"trying to say what something is worth, how much we'll enjoy it,"},{"time":492000,"text":"how much pleasure it will give us."},{"time":495000,"text":"I want to talk now about errors in value."},{"time":497000,"text":"How much is this Big Mac worth? Is it worth 25 dollars?"},{"time":501000,"text":"Most of you have the intuition that it's not --"},{"time":504000,"text":"you wouldn't pay that for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"But in fact, to decide whether a Big Mac is worth 25 dollars requires"},{"time":510000,"text":"that you ask one, and only one question, which is:"},{"time":513000,"text":"What else can I do with 25 dollars?"},{"time":515000,"text":"If you've ever gotten on one of those long-haul flights to Australia"},{"time":519000,"text":"and realized that they're not going to serve you any food,"},{"time":522000,"text":"but somebody in the row in front of you has just opened"},{"time":524000,"text":"the McDonald's bag, and the smell of golden arches"},{"time":527000,"text":"is wafting over the seat, you think,"},{"time":530000,"text":"I can't do anything else with this 25 dollars for 16 hours."},{"time":533000,"text":"I can't even set it on fire -- they took my cigarette lighter!"},{"time":536000,"text":"Suddenly, 25 dollars for a Big Mac might be a good deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":539000,"text":"On the other hand, if you're visiting an underdeveloped country,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and 25 dollars buys you a gourmet meal, it's exorbitant for a Big Mac."},{"time":545000,"text":"Why were you all sure that the answer to the question was no,"},{"time":548000,"text":"before I'd even told you anything about the context?"},{"time":551000,"text":"Because most of you compared the price of this Big Mac"},{"time":555000,"text":"to the price you're used to paying. Rather than asking,"},{"time":558000,"text":"\"What else can I do with my money,\" comparing this investment"},{"time":561000,"text":"to other possible investments, you compared to the past."},{"time":565000,"text":"And this is a systematic error people make."},{"time":567000,"text":"What you knew is, you paid three dollars in the past; 25 is outrageous."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572000,"text":"This is an error, and I can prove it to you by showing"},{"time":574000,"text":"the kinds of irrationalities to which it leads."},{"time":576000,"text":"For example, this is, of course,"},{"time":579000,"text":"one of the most delicious tricks in marketing,"},{"time":581000,"text":"is to say something used to be higher,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and suddenly it seems like a very good deal."},{"time":586000,"text":"When people are asked about these two different jobs:"},{"time":589000,"text":"a job where you make 60K, then 50K, then 40K,"},{"time":592000,"text":"a job where you're getting a salary cut each year,"},{"time":594000,"text":"and one in which you're getting a salary increase,"},{"time":596000,"text":"people like the second job better than the first, despite the fact"},{"time":600000,"text":"they're all told they make much less money. Why?"},{"time":603000,"text":"Because they had the sense that declining wages are worse"},{"time":607000,"text":"than rising wages, even when the total amount of wages is higher"},{"time":611000,"text":"in the declining period. Here's another nice example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":615000,"text":"Here's a $2,000 Hawaiian vacation package; it's now on sale for 1,600."},{"time":620000,"text":"Assuming you wanted to go to Hawaii, would you buy this package?"},{"time":623000,"text":"Most people say they would. Here's a slightly different story:"},{"time":627000,"text":"$2,000 Hawaiian vacation package is now on sale for 700 dollars,"},{"time":631000,"text":"so you decide to mull it over for a week."},{"time":633000,"text":"By the time you get to the ticket agency, the best fares are gone --"},{"time":635000,"text":"the package now costs 1,500. Would you buy it? Most people say, no."},{"time":640000,"text":"Why? Because it used to cost 700, and there's no way I'm paying 1,500"},{"time":644000,"text":"for something that was 700 last week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"This tendency to compare to the past"},{"time":649000,"text":"is causing people to pass up the better deal. In other words,"},{"time":653000,"text":"a good deal that used to be a great deal is not nearly as good"},{"time":656000,"text":"as an awful deal that was once a horrible deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660000,"text":"Here's another example of how comparing to the past"},{"time":662000,"text":"can befuddle our decisions."},{"time":666000,"text":"Imagine that you're going to the theater."},{"time":668000,"text":"You're on your way to the theater."},{"time":669000,"text":"In your wallet you have a ticket, for which you paid 20 dollars."},{"time":671000,"text":"You also have a 20-dollar bill."},{"time":673000,"text":"When you arrive at the theater,"},{"time":675000,"text":"you discover that somewhere along the way you've lost the ticket."},{"time":678000,"text":"Would you spend your remaining money on replacing it?"},{"time":681000,"text":"Most people answer, no."},{"time":684000,"text":"Now, let's just change one thing in this scenario."},{"time":687000,"text":"You're on your way to the theater,"},{"time":688000,"text":"and in your wallet you have two 20-dollar bills."},{"time":690000,"text":"When you arrive you discover you've lost one of them."},{"time":692000,"text":"Would you spend your remaining 20 dollars on a ticket?"},{"time":694000,"text":"Well, of course, I went to the theater to see the play."},{"time":697000,"text":"What does the loss of 20 dollars along the way have to do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700000,"text":"Now, just in case you're not getting it,"},{"time":703000,"text":"here's a schematic of what happened, OK?"},{"time":705000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":706000,"text":"Along the way, you lost something."},{"time":708000,"text":"In both cases, it was a piece of paper."},{"time":710000,"text":"In one case, it had a U.S. president on it; in the other case it didn't."},{"time":714000,"text":"What the hell difference should it make?"},{"time":716000,"text":"The difference is that when you lost the ticket you say to yourself,"},{"time":719000,"text":"I'm not paying twice for the same thing."},{"time":721000,"text":"You compare the cost of the play now -- 40 dollars --"},{"time":724000,"text":"to the cost that it used to have -- 20 dollars -- and you say it's a bad deal."},{"time":729000,"text":"Comparing with the past causes many of the problems"},{"time":733000,"text":"that behavioral economists and psychologists identify"},{"time":736000,"text":"in people's attempts to assign value."},{"time":738000,"text":"But even when we compare with the possible, instead of the past,"},{"time":743000,"text":"we still make certain kinds of mistakes."},{"time":745000,"text":"And I'm going to show you one or two of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747000,"text":"One of the things we know about comparison:"},{"time":750000,"text":"that when we compare one thing to the other, it changes its value."},{"time":753000,"text":"So in 1992, this fellow, George Bush, for those of us who were"},{"time":757000,"text":"kind of on the liberal side of the political spectrum,"},{"time":760000,"text":"didn't seem like such a great guy."},{"time":762000,"text":"Suddenly, we're almost longing for him to return."},{"time":766000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":769000,"text":"The comparison changes how we evaluate him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"Now, retailers knew this long before anybody else did, of course,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and they use this wisdom to help you --"},{"time":778000,"text":"spare you the undue burden of money."},{"time":780000,"text":"And so a retailer, if you were to go into a wine shop"},{"time":783000,"text":"and you had to buy a bottle of wine,"},{"time":784000,"text":"and you see them here for eight, 27 and 33 dollars, what would you do?"},{"time":788000,"text":"Most people don't want the most expensive,"},{"time":790000,"text":"they don't want the least expensive."},{"time":792000,"text":"So, they will opt for the item in the middle."},{"time":794000,"text":"If you're a smart retailer, then, you will put a very expensive item"},{"time":797000,"text":"that nobody will ever buy on the shelf,"},{"time":799000,"text":"because suddenly the $33 wine doesn't look as expensive in comparison."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"So I'm telling you something you already knew:"},{"time":806000,"text":"namely, that comparison changes the value of things."},{"time":810000,"text":"Here's why that's a problem:"},{"time":811000,"text":"the problem is that when you get that $33 bottle of wine home,"},{"time":817000,"text":"it won't matter what it used to be sitting on the shelf next to."},{"time":821000,"text":"The comparisons we make when we are appraising value,"},{"time":826000,"text":"where we're trying to estimate how much we'll like things,"},{"time":830000,"text":"are not the same comparisons we'll be making when we consume them."},{"time":833000,"text":"This problem of shifting comparisons can bedevil"},{"time":837000,"text":"our attempts to make rational decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840000,"text":"Let me just give you an example."},{"time":841000,"text":"I have to show you something from my own lab, so let me sneak this in."},{"time":845000,"text":"These are subjects coming to an experiment to be asked"},{"time":847000,"text":"the simplest of all questions:"},{"time":849000,"text":"How much will you enjoy eating potato chips one minute from now?"},{"time":853000,"text":"They're sitting in a room with potato chips in front of them."},{"time":856000,"text":"For some of the subjects, sitting in the far corner of a room"},{"time":859000,"text":"is a box of Godiva chocolates, and for others is a can of Spam."},{"time":864000,"text":"In fact, these items that are sitting in the room change"},{"time":868000,"text":"how much the subjects think they're going to enjoy the potato chips."},{"time":871000,"text":"Namely, those who are looking at Spam"},{"time":873000,"text":"think potato chips are going to be quite tasty;"},{"time":875000,"text":"those who are looking at Godiva chocolate"},{"time":877000,"text":"think they won't be nearly so tasty."},{"time":879000,"text":"Of course, what happens when they eat the potato chips?"},{"time":881000,"text":"Well, look, you didn't need a psychologist to tell you that"},{"time":884000,"text":"when you have a mouthful of greasy, salty, crispy, delicious snacks,"},{"time":888000,"text":"what's sitting in the corner of the room"},{"time":889000,"text":"makes not a damn bit of difference to your gustatory experience."},{"time":894000,"text":"Nonetheless, their predictions are perverted by a comparison"},{"time":898000,"text":"that then does not carry through and change their experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"You've all experienced this yourself, even if you've never come"},{"time":904000,"text":"into our lab to eat potato chips. So here's a question:"},{"time":907000,"text":"You want to buy a car stereo."},{"time":909000,"text":"The dealer near your house sells this particular stereo for 200 dollars,"},{"time":914000,"text":"but if you drive across town, you can get it for 100 bucks."},{"time":917000,"text":"So would you drive to get 50 percent off, saving 100 dollars?"},{"time":920000,"text":"Most people say they would."},{"time":922000,"text":"They can't imagine buying it for twice the price"},{"time":924000,"text":"when, with one trip across town, they can get it for half off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Now, let's imagine instead you wanted to buy a car that had a stereo,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and the dealer near your house had it for 31,000."},{"time":934000,"text":"But if you drove across town, you could get it for 30,900."},{"time":939000,"text":"Would you drive to get it? At this point, 0.003 savings -- the 100 dollars."},{"time":943000,"text":"Most people say, no, I'm going to schlep across town"},{"time":945000,"text":"to save 100 bucks on the purchase of a car?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":948000,"text":"This kind of thinking drives economists crazy, and it should."},{"time":952000,"text":"Because this 100 dollars that you save -- hello! --"},{"time":956000,"text":"doesn't know where it came from."},{"time":958000,"text":"It doesn't know what you saved it on."},{"time":960000,"text":"When you go to buy groceries with it, it doesn't go,"},{"time":962000,"text":"I'm the money saved on the car stereo, or,"},{"time":965000,"text":"I'm the dumb money saved on the car. It's money."},{"time":969000,"text":"And if a drive across town is worth 100 bucks, it's worth 100 bucks"},{"time":972000,"text":"no matter what you're saving it on. People don't think that way."},{"time":975000,"text":"That's why they don't know whether their mutual fund manager"},{"time":977000,"text":"is taking 0.1 percent or 0.15 percent of their investment,"},{"time":982000,"text":"but they clip coupons to save one dollar off of toothpaste."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"Now, you can see, this is the problem of shifting comparisons,"},{"time":988000,"text":"because what you're doing is, you're comparing the 100 bucks"},{"time":991000,"text":"to the purchase that you're making,"},{"time":993000,"text":"but when you go to spend that money you won't be making that comparison."},{"time":997000,"text":"You've all had this experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":999000,"text":"If you're an American, for example, you've probably traveled in France."},{"time":1003000,"text":"And at some point you may have met a couple"},{"time":1005000,"text":"from your own hometown, and you thought,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"\"Oh, my God, these people are so warm. They're so nice to me."},{"time":1011000,"text":"I mean, compared to all these people who hate me"},{"time":1013000,"text":"when I try to speak their language and hate me more when I don't,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"these people are just wonderful.\" And so you tour France with them,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"and then you get home and you invite them over for dinner,"},{"time":1021000,"text":"and what do you find?"},{"time":1022000,"text":"Compared to your regular friends,"},{"time":1024000,"text":"they are boring and dull, right? Because in this new context,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"the comparison is very, very different. In fact, you find yourself"},{"time":1032000,"text":"disliking them enough almost to qualify for French citizenship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036000,"text":"Now, you have exactly the same problem when you shop for a stereo."},{"time":1039000,"text":"You go to the stereo store, you see two sets of speakers --"},{"time":1042000,"text":"these big, boxy, monoliths, and these little, sleek speakers,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"and you play them, and you go, you know, I do hear a difference:"},{"time":1048000,"text":"the big ones sound a little better."},{"time":1050000,"text":"And so you buy them, and you bring them home,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"and you entirely violate the décor of your house."},{"time":1055000,"text":"And the problem, of course, is that this comparison you made in the store"},{"time":1059000,"text":"is a comparison you'll never make again."},{"time":1061000,"text":"What are the odds that years later you'll turn on the stereo and go,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"\"Sounds so much better than those little ones,\""},{"time":1066000,"text":"which you can't even remember hearing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"The problem of shifting comparisons is even more difficult"},{"time":1071000,"text":"when these choices are arrayed over time."},{"time":1074000,"text":"People have a lot of trouble making decisions"},{"time":1077000,"text":"about things that will happen at different points in time."},{"time":1080000,"text":"And what psychologists and behavioral economists have discovered"},{"time":1082000,"text":"is that by and large people use two simple rules."},{"time":1085000,"text":"So let me give you one very easy problem, a second very easy problem"},{"time":1089000,"text":"and then a third, hard, problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1090000,"text":"Here's the first easy problem:"},{"time":1093000,"text":"You can have 60 dollars now or 50 dollars now. Which would you prefer?"},{"time":1096000,"text":"This is what we call a one-item IQ test, OK?"},{"time":1099000,"text":"All of us, I hope, prefer more money, and the reason is,"},{"time":1102000,"text":"we believe more is better than less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"Here's the second problem:"},{"time":1106000,"text":"You can have 60 dollars today or 60 dollars in a month. Which would you prefer?"},{"time":1110000,"text":"Again, an easy decision,"},{"time":1112000,"text":"because we all know that now is better than later."},{"time":1116000,"text":"What's hard in our decision-making is when these two rules conflict."},{"time":1119000,"text":"For example, when you're offered 50 dollars now or 60 dollars in a month."},{"time":1123000,"text":"This typifies a lot of situations in life in which you will gain"},{"time":1126000,"text":"by waiting, but you have to be patient."},{"time":1129000,"text":"What do we know? What do people do in these kinds of situations?"},{"time":1132000,"text":"Well, by and large people are enormously impatient."},{"time":1136000,"text":"That is, they require interest rates in the hundred"},{"time":1139000,"text":"or thousands of percents in order to delay gratification"},{"time":1143000,"text":"and wait until next month for the extra 10 dollars."},{"time":1147000,"text":"Maybe that isn't so remarkable, but what is remarkable is"},{"time":1150000,"text":"how easy it is to make this impatience go away by simply changing"},{"time":1154000,"text":"when the delivery of these monetary units will happen."},{"time":1158000,"text":"Imagine that you can have 50 dollars in a year -- that's 12 months --"},{"time":1161000,"text":"or 60 dollars in 13 months."},{"time":1164000,"text":"What do we find now?"},{"time":1165000,"text":"People are gladly willing to wait: as long as they're waiting 12,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"they might as well wait 13."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1170000,"text":"What makes this dynamic inconsistency happen?"},{"time":1173000,"text":"Comparison. Troubling comparison. Let me show you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"This is just a graph showing the results that I just suggested"},{"time":1180000,"text":"you would show if I gave you time to respond, which is,"},{"time":1182000,"text":"people find that the subjective value of 50 is higher"},{"time":1185000,"text":"than the subjective value of 60 when they'll be delivered in now"},{"time":1189000,"text":"or one month, respectively -- a 30-day delay --"},{"time":1191000,"text":"but they show the reverse pattern when you push the entire decision"},{"time":1195000,"text":"off into the future a year."},{"time":1198000,"text":"Now, why in the world do you get this pattern of results?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1202000,"text":"These guys can tell us."},{"time":1203000,"text":"What you see here are two lads,"},{"time":1206000,"text":"one of them larger than the other: the fireman and the fiddler."},{"time":1209000,"text":"They are going to recede towards the vanishing point in the horizon,"},{"time":1212000,"text":"and I want you to notice two things."},{"time":1214000,"text":"At no point will the fireman look taller than the fiddler. No point."},{"time":1220000,"text":"However, the difference between them seems to be getting smaller."},{"time":1223000,"text":"First it's an inch in your view, then it's a quarter-inch,"},{"time":1226000,"text":"then a half-inch, and then finally they go off the edge of the earth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1230000,"text":"Here are the results of what I just showed you."},{"time":1233000,"text":"This is the subjective height --"},{"time":1235000,"text":"the height you saw of these guys at various points."},{"time":1238000,"text":"And I want you to see that two things are true."},{"time":1240000,"text":"One, the farther away they are, the smaller they look;"},{"time":1243000,"text":"and two, the fireman is always bigger than the fiddler."},{"time":1245000,"text":"But watch what happens when we make some of them disappear. Right."},{"time":1251000,"text":"At a very close distance, the fiddler looks taller than the fireman,"},{"time":1254000,"text":"but at a far distance"},{"time":1256000,"text":"their normal, their true, relations are preserved."},{"time":1259000,"text":"As Plato said, what space is to size, time is to value."},{"time":1264000,"text":"These are the results of the hard problem I gave you:"},{"time":1269000,"text":"60 now or 50 in a month?"},{"time":1271000,"text":"And these are subjective values,"},{"time":1272000,"text":"and what you can see is, our two rules are preserved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1274000,"text":"People always think more is better than less:"},{"time":1276000,"text":"60 is always better than 50,"},{"time":1278000,"text":"and they always think now is better than later:"},{"time":1280000,"text":"the bars on this side are higher than the bars on this side."},{"time":1283000,"text":"Watch what happens when we drop some out."},{"time":1286000,"text":"Suddenly we have the dynamic inconsistency that puzzled us."},{"time":1289000,"text":"We have the tendency for people to go for 50 dollars now"},{"time":1293000,"text":"over waiting a month, but not if that decision is far in the future."},{"time":1296000,"text":"Notice something interesting that this implies -- namely, that"},{"time":1300000,"text":"when people get to the future, they will change their minds."},{"time":1304000,"text":"That is, as that month 12 approaches, you will say,"},{"time":1307000,"text":"what was I thinking, waiting an extra month for 60 dollars?"},{"time":1310000,"text":"I'll take the 50 dollars now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1313000,"text":"Well, the question with which I'd like to end is this:"},{"time":1316000,"text":"If we're so damn stupid, how did we get to the moon?"},{"time":1319000,"text":"Because I could go on for about two hours with evidence"},{"time":1322000,"text":"of people's inability to estimate odds and inability to estimate value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1328000,"text":"The answer to this question, I think, is an answer you've already heard"},{"time":1330000,"text":"in some of the talks, and I dare say you will hear again:"},{"time":1332000,"text":"namely, that our brains were evolved for a very different world"},{"time":1336000,"text":"than the one in which we are living."},{"time":1338000,"text":"They were evolved for a world"},{"time":1340000,"text":"in which people lived in very small groups,"},{"time":1342000,"text":"rarely met anybody who was terribly different from themselves,"},{"time":1345000,"text":"had rather short lives in which there were few choices"},{"time":1348000,"text":"and the highest priority was to eat and mate today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1353000,"text":"Bernoulli's gift, Bernoulli's little formula, allows us, it tells us"},{"time":1358000,"text":"how we should think in a world for which nature never designed us."},{"time":1363000,"text":"That explains why we are so bad at using it, but it also explains"},{"time":1367000,"text":"why it is so terribly important that we become good, fast."},{"time":1372000,"text":"We are the only species on this planet"},{"time":1374000,"text":"that has ever held its own fate in its hands."},{"time":1378000,"text":"We have no significant predators,"},{"time":1380000,"text":"we're the masters of our physical environment;"},{"time":1382000,"text":"the things that normally cause species to become extinct"},{"time":1385000,"text":"are no longer any threat to us."},{"time":1388000,"text":"The only thing -- the only thing -- that can destroy us and doom us"},{"time":1393000,"text":"are our own decisions."},{"time":1395000,"text":"If we're not here in 10,000 years, it's going to be because"},{"time":1399000,"text":"we could not take advantage of the gift given to us"},{"time":1403000,"text":"by a young Dutch fellow in 1738,"},{"time":1406000,"text":"because we underestimated the odds of our future pains"},{"time":1410000,"text":"and overestimated the value of our present pleasures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1414000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1415000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1425000,"text":"Chris Anderson: That was remarkable."},{"time":1428000,"text":"We have time for some questions for Dan Gilbert. One and two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1433000,"text":"Bill Lyell: Would you say that this mechanism"},{"time":1436000,"text":"is in part how terrorism actually works to frighten us,"},{"time":1440000,"text":"and is there some way that we could counteract that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1444000,"text":"Dan Gilbert: I actually was consulting recently"},{"time":1445000,"text":"with the Department of Homeland Security, which generally believes"},{"time":1448000,"text":"that American security dollars should go to making borders safer."},{"time":1452000,"text":"I tried to point out to them that terrorism was a name"},{"time":1455000,"text":"based on people's psychological reaction to a set of events,"},{"time":1459000,"text":"and that if they were concerned about terrorism they might ask"},{"time":1461000,"text":"what causes terror and how can we stop people from being terrified,"},{"time":1464000,"text":"rather than -- not rather than, but in addition to"},{"time":1467000,"text":"stopping the atrocities that we're all concerned about."},{"time":1470000,"text":"Surely the kinds of play that at least American media give to --"},{"time":1476000,"text":"and forgive me, but in raw numbers these are very tiny accidents."},{"time":1481000,"text":"We already know, for example, in the United States,"},{"time":1483000,"text":"more people have died as a result of not taking airplanes --"},{"time":1487000,"text":"because they were scared -- and driving on highways,"},{"time":1489000,"text":"than were killed in 9/11. OK?"},{"time":1491000,"text":"If I told you that there was a plague"},{"time":1493000,"text":"that was going to kill 15,000 Americans next year,"},{"time":1496000,"text":"you might be alarmed if you didn't find out it was the flu."},{"time":1499000,"text":"These are small-scale accidents, and we should be wondering"},{"time":1502000,"text":"whether they should get the kind of play,"},{"time":1504000,"text":"the kind of coverage, that they do."},{"time":1506000,"text":"Surely that causes people to overestimate the likelihood"},{"time":1509000,"text":"that they'll be hurt in these various ways,"},{"time":1511000,"text":"and gives power to the very people who want to frighten us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1513000,"text":"CA: Dan, I'd like to hear more on this. So, you're saying"},{"time":1515000,"text":"that our response to terror is, I mean, it's a form of mental bug?"},{"time":1519000,"text":"Talk more about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1520000,"text":"DG: It's out-sized. I mean, look."},{"time":1523000,"text":"If Australia disappears tomorrow,"},{"time":1525000,"text":"terror is probably the right response."},{"time":1527000,"text":"That's an awful large lot of very nice people. On the other hand,"},{"time":1532000,"text":"when a bus blows up and 30 people are killed,"},{"time":1535000,"text":"more people than that were killed"},{"time":1537000,"text":"by not using their seatbelts in the same country."},{"time":1540000,"text":"Is terror the right response?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1541000,"text":"CA: What causes the bug? Is it the drama of the event --"},{"time":1545000,"text":"that it's so spectacular?"},{"time":1546000,"text":"Is it the fact that it's an intentional attack by, quote, outsiders?"},{"time":1549000,"text":"What is it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1550000,"text":"DG: Yes. It's a number of things, and you hit on several of them."},{"time":1553000,"text":"First, it's a human agent trying to kill us --"},{"time":1555000,"text":"it's not a tree falling on us by accident."},{"time":1558000,"text":"Second, these are enemies who may want to strike and hurt us again."},{"time":1561000,"text":"People are being killed for no reason instead of good reason --"},{"time":1564000,"text":"as if there's good reason, but sometimes people think there are."},{"time":1567000,"text":"So there are a number of things that together"},{"time":1569000,"text":"make this seem like a fantastic event, but let's not play down"},{"time":1572000,"text":"the fact that newspapers sell when people see something in it"},{"time":1576000,"text":"they want to read. So there's a large role here played by the media,"},{"time":1579000,"text":"who want these things to be"},{"time":1581000,"text":"as spectacular as they possibly can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1585000,"text":"CA: I mean, what would it take to persuade our culture to downplay it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1591000,"text":"DG: Well, go to Israel. You know,"},{"time":1592000,"text":"go to Israel. And a mall blows up,"},{"time":1594000,"text":"and then everybody's unhappy about it, and an hour-and-a-half later --"},{"time":1597000,"text":"at least when I was there, and I was 150 feet from the mall"},{"time":1600000,"text":"when it blew up -- I went back to my hotel"},{"time":1602000,"text":"and the wedding that was planned was still going on."},{"time":1605000,"text":"And as the Israeli mother said,"},{"time":1606000,"text":"she said, \"We never let them win by stopping weddings.\""},{"time":1610000,"text":"I mean, this is a society that has learned --"},{"time":1611000,"text":"and there are others too -- that has learned to live"},{"time":1613000,"text":"with a certain amount of terrorism and not be quite as upset by it,"},{"time":1618000,"text":"shall I say, as those of us who have not had many terror attacks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1621000,"text":"CA: But is there a rational fear that actually,"},{"time":1624000,"text":"the reason we're frightened about this is because we think that"},{"time":1627000,"text":"the Big One is to come?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1628000,"text":"DG: Yes, of course. So, if we knew that this was the worst attack"},{"time":1632000,"text":"there would ever be, there might be more and more buses of 30 people --"},{"time":1636000,"text":"we would probably not be nearly so frightened."},{"time":1638000,"text":"I don't want to say -- please, I'm going to get quoted somewhere"},{"time":1640000,"text":"as saying, \"Terrorism is fine and we shouldn't be so distressed.\""},{"time":1644000,"text":"That's not my point at all."},{"time":1646000,"text":"What I'm saying is that, surely, rationally,"},{"time":1648000,"text":"our distress about things that happen, about threats,"},{"time":1652000,"text":"should be roughly proportional to the size of those threats"},{"time":1655000,"text":"and threats to come."},{"time":1657000,"text":"I think in the case of terrorism, it isn't."},{"time":1660000,"text":"And many of the things we've heard about from our speakers today --"},{"time":1662000,"text":"how many people do you know got up and said,"},{"time":1664000,"text":"Poverty! I can't believe what poverty is doing to us."},{"time":1668000,"text":"People get up in the morning; they don't care about poverty."},{"time":1670000,"text":"It's not making headlines, it's not making news, it's not flashy."},{"time":1672000,"text":"There are no guns going off."},{"time":1674000,"text":"I mean, if you had to solve one of these problems, Chris,"},{"time":1676000,"text":"which would you solve? Terrorism or poverty?"},{"time":1678000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1682000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1684000,"text":"That's a tough one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1686000,"text":"CA: There's no question."},{"time":1687000,"text":"Poverty, by an order of magnitude, a huge order of magnitude,"},{"time":1691000,"text":"unless someone can show that there's, you know,"},{"time":1694000,"text":"terrorists with a nuke are really likely to come."},{"time":1698000,"text":"The latest I've read, seen, thought"},{"time":1700000,"text":"is that it's incredibly hard for them to do that."},{"time":1704000,"text":"If that turns out to be wrong, we all look silly,"},{"time":1706000,"text":"but with poverty it's a bit --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1708000,"text":"DG: Even if that were true, still more people die from poverty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1715000,"text":"CA: We've evolved to get all excited"},{"time":1716000,"text":"about these dramatic attacks. Is that because in the past,"},{"time":1719000,"text":"in the ancient past, we just didn't understand things like disease"},{"time":1722000,"text":"and systems that cause poverty and so forth,"},{"time":1724000,"text":"and so it made no sense for us as a species to put any energy"},{"time":1728000,"text":"into worrying about those things?"},{"time":1730000,"text":"People died; so be it."},{"time":1732000,"text":"But if you got attacked, that was something you could do something about."},{"time":1734000,"text":"And so we evolved these responses."},{"time":1736000,"text":"Is that what happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1737000,"text":"DG: Well, you know, the people who are most skeptical"},{"time":1740000,"text":"about leaping to evolutionary explanations for everything"},{"time":1742000,"text":"are the evolutionary psychologists themselves."},{"time":1744000,"text":"My guess is that there's nothing quite that specific"},{"time":1747000,"text":"in our evolutionary past. But rather, if you're looking for"},{"time":1749000,"text":"an evolutionary explanation, you might say"},{"time":1751000,"text":"that most organisms are neo-phobic -- that is, they're a little scared"},{"time":1755000,"text":"of stuff that's new and different."},{"time":1756000,"text":"And there's a good reason to be,"},{"time":1758000,"text":"because old stuff didn't eat you. Right?"},{"time":1759000,"text":"Any animal you see that you've seen before is less likely"},{"time":1762000,"text":"to be a predator than one that you've never seen before."},{"time":1765000,"text":"So, you know, when a school bus is blown up and we've never seen this before,"},{"time":1768000,"text":"our general tendency is to orient towards"},{"time":1770000,"text":"that which is new and novel is activated."},{"time":1775000,"text":"I don't think it's quite as specific a mechanism"},{"time":1777000,"text":"as the one you alluded to, but maybe a more fundamental one underlying it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1783000,"text":"Jay Walker: You know, economists love to talk about"},{"time":1788000,"text":"the stupidity of people who buy lottery tickets. But I suspect"},{"time":1792000,"text":"you're making the exact same error you're accusing those people of,"},{"time":1795000,"text":"which is the error of value."},{"time":1796000,"text":"I know, because I've interviewed"},{"time":1797000,"text":"about 1,000 lottery buyers over the years."},{"time":1799000,"text":"It turns out that the value of buying a lottery ticket is not winning."},{"time":1803000,"text":"That's what you think it is. All right?"},{"time":1805000,"text":"The average lottery buyer buys about 150 tickets a year,"},{"time":1808000,"text":"so the buyer knows full well that he or she is going to lose,"},{"time":1812000,"text":"and yet she buys 150 tickets a year. Why is that?"},{"time":1815000,"text":"It's not because she is stupid or he is stupid."},{"time":1819000,"text":"It's because the anticipation of possibly winning"},{"time":1822000,"text":"releases serotonin in the brain, and actually provides a good feeling"},{"time":1826000,"text":"until the drawing indicates you've lost."},{"time":1828000,"text":"Or, to put it another way, for the dollar investment,"},{"time":1831000,"text":"you can have a much better feeling than flushing the money"},{"time":1834000,"text":"down the toilet, which you cannot have a good feeling from."},{"time":1837000,"text":"Now, economists tend to --"},{"time":1839000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1842000,"text":"-- economists tend to view the world"},{"time":1843000,"text":"through their own lenses, which is:"},{"time":1845000,"text":"this is just a bunch of stupid people."},{"time":1847000,"text":"And as a result, many people look at economists as stupid people."},{"time":1851000,"text":"And so fundamentally, the reason we got to the moon is,"},{"time":1854000,"text":"we didn't listen to the economists. Thank you very much."},{"time":1857000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1862000,"text":"DG: Well, no, it's a great point. It remains to be seen"},{"time":1865000,"text":"whether the joy of anticipation is exactly equaled"},{"time":1869000,"text":"by the amount of disappointment after the lottery. Because remember,"},{"time":1872000,"text":"people who didn't buy tickets don't feel awful the next day either,"},{"time":1875000,"text":"even though they don't feel great during the drawing."},{"time":1877000,"text":"I would disagree that people know they're not going to win."},{"time":1879000,"text":"I think they think it's unlikely, but it could happen,"},{"time":1882000,"text":"which is why they prefer that to the flushing."},{"time":1885000,"text":"But certainly I see your point: that there can be"},{"time":1888000,"text":"some utility to buying a lottery ticket other than winning."},{"time":1892000,"text":"Now, I think there's many good reasons not to listen to economists."},{"time":1895000,"text":"That isn't one of them, for me, but there's many others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1898000,"text":"CA: Last question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1900000,"text":"Aubrey de Grey: My name's Aubrey de Grey, from Cambridge."},{"time":1903000,"text":"I work on the thing that kills more people than anything else kills --"},{"time":1907000,"text":"I work on aging -- and I'm interested in doing something about it,"},{"time":1909000,"text":"as we'll all hear tomorrow."},{"time":1910000,"text":"I very much resonate with what you're saying,"},{"time":1913000,"text":"because it seems to me that the problem"},{"time":1915000,"text":"with getting people interested in doing anything about aging"},{"time":1918000,"text":"is that by the time aging is about to kill you it looks like cancer"},{"time":1921000,"text":"or heart disease or whatever. Do you have any advice?"},{"time":1924000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1927000,"text":"DG: For you or for them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1928000,"text":"AdG: In persuading them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1929000,"text":"DG: Ah, for you in persuading them."},{"time":1931000,"text":"Well, it's notoriously difficult to get people to be farsighted."},{"time":1934000,"text":"But one thing that psychologists have tried that seems to work"},{"time":1938000,"text":"is to get people to imagine the future more vividly."},{"time":1941000,"text":"One of the problems with making decisions about the far future"},{"time":1944000,"text":"and the near future is that we imagine the near future"},{"time":1947000,"text":"much more vividly than the far future."},{"time":1949000,"text":"To the extent that you can equalize the amount of detail"},{"time":1953000,"text":"that people put into the mental representations"},{"time":1955000,"text":"of near and far future, people begin to make decisions"},{"time":1957000,"text":"about the two in the same way."},{"time":1959000,"text":"So, would you like to have an extra 100,000 dollars when you're 65"},{"time":1964000,"text":"is a question that's very different than,"},{"time":1965000,"text":"imagine who you'll be when you're 65: will you be living,"},{"time":1969000,"text":"what will you look like, how much hair will you have,"},{"time":1971000,"text":"who will you be living with."},{"time":1972000,"text":"Once we have all the details of that imaginary scenario,"},{"time":1975000,"text":"suddenly we feel like it might be important to save"},{"time":1977000,"text":"so that that guy has a little retirement money."},{"time":1980000,"text":"But these are tricks around the margins."},{"time":1982000,"text":"I think in general you're battling a very fundamental human tendency,"},{"time":1985000,"text":"which is to say, \"I'm here today,"},{"time":1987000,"text":"and so now is more important than later.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1990000,"text":"CA: Dan, thank you. Members of the audience,"},{"time":1992000,"text":"that was a fantastic session. Thank you."},{"time":1993000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}